---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
import ImagePlaceholder from '../components/ImagePlaceholder.astro';
import FirstSteps from '../components/FirstSteps.astro';

const checklist = [
	'A phone or computer',
	'A private spot where you can talk freely',
	'Headphones if you want extra privacy',
	'That’s it',
];
---

<Layout
	title="How Online Therapy Sessions Work | Custom Counseling"
	description="What to expect from online counseling: secure Google Meet sessions, simple setup, and the same conversation you'd have in an office — from home."
>
	<PageHero
		heading="How Online Sessions Work"
		subhead="The same conversation you'd have in an office, from the comfort of home."
	/>

	<section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-14 sm:px-6 md:py-20">
		<div class="prose-site text-lg">
			<p>
				<strong>Online counseling can be just as effective as in-person.</strong> You can meet me
				wherever you are. Social anxiety, time constraints, crippling depression, whatever makes
				leaving the house hard, none of it has to stand between you and getting help.
			</p>
			<!-- DRAFT (open item O4): swap in Eric's own elevator pitch for why online works. -->
			<p>
				Some of my clients open up more from their own couch than they ever did in an office.
				Your space is familiar. That helps.
			</p>
		</div>

		<h2 class="mt-12 text-3xl">What a first session looks like</h2>
		<ol class="mt-6 space-y-4">
			<li class="flex gap-4">
				<span aria-hidden="true" class="flex h-9 w-9 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-clay-400 font-display font-semibold text-ink-950">1</span>
				<p class="pt-1">After our free 15-minute phone call, I email you a couple of forms to sign. No portals, no passwords.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="flex gap-4">
				<span aria-hidden="true" class="flex h-9 w-9 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-clay-400 font-display font-semibold text-ink-950">2</span>
				<p class="pt-1">Before our session, I send you a secure Google Meet link. Click it at our time, and we're talking.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="flex gap-4">
				<span aria-hidden="true" class="flex h-9 w-9 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-clay-400 font-display font-semibold text-ink-950">3</span>
				<p class="pt-1">The first session or two is about getting to know each other. Then we create a plan for the goals you see fit.</p>
			</li>
		</ol>

		<div class="mt-12 grid items-center gap-10 md:grid-cols-2">
			<div>
				<h2 class="text-3xl">What you need</h2>
				<ul class="mt-5 space-y-3">
					{
						checklist.map((item) => (
							<li class="flex items-center gap-3">
								<span aria-hidden="true" class="h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-clay-400" />
								{item}
							</li>
						))
					}
				</ul>
			</div>
			<ImagePlaceholder label="Photo — session setup at home" />
		</div>

		<div class="prose-site mt-12 text-lg">
			<h2 class="text-3xl">Couples over video</h2>
			<p>
				Most couples join together on one screen at home. Separate devices work too, even if one
				of you is traveling. We'll figure out what works best for you both.
			</p>

			<h2 class="text-3xl">Is it private?</h2>
			<p>
				Yes. Sessions happen over a secure Google Meet link, and what we talk about stays between
				us, the same as it would in an office.
			</p>

			<h2 class="text-3xl">What if the tech acts up?</h2>
			<!-- DRAFT (open item O5): confirm Eric's actual tech-failure policy. -->
			<p>
				If the call drops, I'll send a fresh link right away. If we can't reconnect, we finish by
				phone or reschedule the remaining time at no charge.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<FirstSteps />
</Layout>
